{"title_page": "Hero (2019 Tamil film)", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian 2019 Tamil-language superhero action thriller film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Hero\n| image          = Hero film poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[P. S. Mithran]]\n| producer       = Kotapadi J. Rajesh<br />T. Ezhumalaiyan\n| writer         = P. S. Mithran<br />[[Pon Parthiban]]<br />Savari Muthu<br />Antony Bhagyaraj\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Sivakarthikeyan]]\n*[[Abhay Deol]]<!-- DO NOT EDIT THE ORDER OF THE CAST. This is how the credits appeared in the movie-->\n*[[Arjun Sarja|Arjun]]\n*[[Kalyani Priyadarshan]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cinematography = [[George C. Williams (cinematographer)|George C. Williams]]\n| editing        = [[Ruben (editor)|Ruben]]\n| studio         = KJR Studios\n| released       = {{film date|2019|12|20|df=yes|}}\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = 25 Crores <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.seelatest.com/tamil/hero-tamil-movie-box-office-collection-day-1-sivakarthikeyan-film-added-mixed-response-on-opening-day|title=Movie Hero Budget}}</ref>\n| gross          = 36.89 Crores <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.southfdfs.in/2019/12/hero-movie-worldwide-boxoffice.html\n |title=Movie Hero Gross}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Hero''''' is a 2019 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[superhero film]] directed by [[P. S. Mithran]], and produced by Kotapadi J. Rajesh under his production house KJR Studios. It stars [[Sivakarthikeyan]], [[Abhay Deol]], [[Arjun Sarja|Arjun]], [[Kalyani Priyadarshan]] and [[Ivana (actress)|Ivana]] in prominent roles. This film marks the Tamil debuts of Deol and Kalyani Priyadarshan.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/sivakarthikeyans-next-film-sk15-with-ps-mithran-is-titled-hero.html|title=Sivakarthikeyan's next film SK15 with PS Mithran is titled Hero|date=13 March 2019|website=Behindwoods}}</ref>\n\nThe story was written by P. S. Mithran, [[Pon Parthiban]], Savari Muthu and Antony Bhagyaraj. The music for the film is composed by [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]], with cinematography done by [[George C. Williams (cinematographer)|George C. Williams]], and editing done by [[Ruben (editor)|Ruben]]. The film was released worldwide on 20 December 2019.<ref name=\"reldate\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2019/sep/10/abhay-deols-tamil-film-hero-release-date-out-2031504.html|title=Abhay Deol's Tamil film 'Hero' release date out!|website=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nSakthivel \"Sakthi\" is a young boy who dreams of becoming a superhero, like [[Shaktimaan]]. After being ridiculed by his teacher and classmates for believing that Shaktimaan is real, Sakthi tries to prove it by falling off the terrace of his school, injuring himself in the process. His father ([[Azhagam Perumal]]) tries to convince Sakthi that Shaktimaan is fictional by showing the disclaimer of actor [[Mukesh Khanna]] advising viewers that the events depicted in the show are purely fictitious, causing Sakthi to abandon his hopes of becoming a superhero.\n \nYears later, Sakthi ([[Sivakarthikeyan]]) and Inbaraj \"Ink\" ([[Robo Shankar]]) are friends who earn their livelihood as educational brokers and run a xerox shop in their neighbourhood that houses a certificate [[forgery]] unit to help the needy secure their desired jobs at the expense of huge commissions. Sakthi bumps across Meera ([[Kalyani Priyadarshan]]), a social worker at an educational fair. and falls in love with her. Meera happens to be the inspiration of Mathi ([[Ivana (actress)|Ivana]]), a brilliant girl who aspires to become an [[aerospace engineering|aeronautical engineer]]. Mathi devises an engine that runs on saltwater as a measure to help her father ([[Elango Kumaravel]]) and many other thwart the problem of rising petrol prices. Meera soon learns of Sakthi's true profession and advises him to help Mathi secure an admission in an engineering college without any payment. Sakthi tries to secure an admission for Mathi, but to no avail. He learns that the only way to help Mathi secure a seat is to demonstrate the practical applications of her engine, which is rejected by Sathyamoorthy ([[Arjun Sarja|Arjun]]), Mathi's teacher who runs a school for the academically weak but brilliant children. Sakthi bypasses his warnings and demonstrates the engine at an educational fair by attaching it to an autorickshaw. This attracts the attention of the henchman of Mahadev ([[Abhay Deol]]). In turn, he promises a seat for Mathi with full scholarship. The next day, the autorickshaw is seized by the police, and Mathi is arrested on grounds of patent violation. The court convicts her guilty of the charges, which distraughts her. She attempts suicide by falling off a running train. Sakthi takes her to the hospital, only for the doctors to delay her treatment, and she eventually succumbs to her injuries. Sakthi and Ink are also convicted guilty and are placed on the wanted list for aiding Madhi. \n\nSakthi, on the run, decides that the only way to avenge Mathi's death and prove her innocence is to confront the company issuing the patents. Due to his experience in forging certificates, he easily fishes out the fact that the patent was forged by the company under Mahadev's orders but is attacked in the process, when he is rescued by Sathyamoorthy wearing a mask. Sathyamoorthy explains to him that Mahadev is a corrupt business tycoon whose aim is to wipe out innovation in work culture. He also subdues brilliant students and subjects them to [[lobotomy]], rendering their [[frontal cortex]] unusable, therefore reducing them to his \"puppets\". He uses their innovations to sell them to foreign companies and earn profits. Sathyamoorthy, being an advocate of innovation, secretly nurtures such children away from Mahadev in his school. Sakthi decides to fight the system along with Sathyamoorthy and the children, donning the mantle of the \"Mask.\"\n\nUsing the gadgets developed by the children and Sathyamoorthy's training, Sakthi fights through Mahadev's henchmen and eventually learns the truth. Sathyamoorthy sacrifices himself in the struggle, prompting Sakthi to telecast the innovative inventions of students and explaining to the audience that children should be given freedom to follow their passion and not be just mere bookworms. In the final fight, Mahadev's plans are foiled and Sakthi subjects him to lobotomy, disabling him permanently. Six months later, Sakthi, while still on the wanted list, runs the school along with Meera on the outskirts of the city. A police officer ([[Prem (actor)|Prem]]) approaches him and takes him in his jeep around the city, where Sakthi finds major developments in the city due to the innovations of Mathi and other brilliant students. The officer tosses away the documents relating to Sakthi's charges as he had opened his eyes about his child's dreams, and requests Sakthi to continue on with the mantle of the Mask.\nIn the post credits scene, it is also revealed that Sathyamoorthy is alive and is helping Sakthi in his missions.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Sivakarthikeyan]] as Sakthivel \"Sakthi\" / Hero (Mask)\n** Master Raghavan as young Sakthivel\n* [[Arjun Sarja|Arjun]] as Sathyamoorthy \"Moorthy\" (Sakthi\u2019s mentor) / Mask\n* [[Abhay Deol]] as Mahadev\n* [[Kalyani Priyadarshan]] as Meera\n* [[Ivana (actress)|Ivana]] as Mathi\n* Shyam Krishnan as Mahadev's assistant\n* [[Robo Shankar]] as Inbaraj \"Ink\"\n* [[Elango Kumaravel]] as Mathi's father\n* [[Azhagam Perumal]] as Sakthi's father\n* [[Prem (actor)|Prem]] as police officer \n* Ray Paul as Sathyamoorthy's student\n* Nithyaraj as Sathyamoorthy's student\n* Raja Rani Pandiyan as a TV viewer\n* Robo Chandru as a TV viewer\n* Shrawan as a TV viewer\n* Priya Rajkumar as a TV viewer\n* Douglas Kumaramoorthy as a private university HR manager\n* Supergood Subramani as the head master of Shakthi's childhood school\n* Mullai as Mullai, a resident of Sakthivel's area\n* Kothandam as a resident of Sakthivel's area\n* \"Black Sheep\" Ayaz as a helpline caller and in a special appearance in the song \"Overa Feel Pannuren\"\n* \"Unakennappa\" Vivek as a helpline caller and in a special appearance in the song \"Overa Feel Pannuren\"\n* P. S. Mithran in a special appearance as a fake certificates dealer\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\nAfter a successful debut through ''[[Irumbu Thirai (2018 film)|Irumbu Thirai]]'', director P. S. Mithran announced in early-2019 that he would direct a film  featuring actor [[Sivakarthikeyan]] in the lead role.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/sivakarthikeyan-ps-mithran-film-officially-announced-90982|title=Sivakarthikeyan-PS Mithran film officially announced|website=The News Minute|date=2 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/exciting-update-on-sivakarthikeyans-next-with-psmithran.html|title=Exciting Update on Sivakarthikeyan's next with P.S.Mithran|date=25 February 2019|website=Behindwoods}}</ref>\n\nThe crew of director Mithran's previous film, ''Irumbu Thirai'' were also retained for this film as well, including composer [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]], editor [[Ruben (editor)|Ruben]], cinematographer [[George C. Williams (cinematographer)|George C. Williams]]. Additionally, [[Arjun Sarja|Arjun]], who was the main antagonist in ''Irumbu Thirai'' was added to the cast.<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/sivakarthikeyan-to-lock-horns-with-arjun-sarja-for-thriller-1380900-2018-11-02|title=Sivakarthikeyan to lock horns with Arjun Sarja for thriller|date= 2 November 2018|website=India Today}}</ref> Furthermore,<ref name=\"auto\"/> later actress [[Kalyani Priyadarshan]] was announced to play the female lead alongside actress [[Ivana (actress)|Ivana]] in a supporting role. The film also marks Abhay Deol's Tamil debut, and he will be playing the main villain role for the first time in his career . <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/young-heroine-joins-the-cast-of-sivakarthikeyans-sk15.html|title=Young heroine joins the cast of Sivakarthikeyan's SK15|date=25 February 2019|website=Behindwoods}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/abhay-deol-plays-villain-in-tamil-film-hero-says-it-was-a-natural-progression-see-pics/story-37Htqb55BCANk46YIcg57J.html|title=Abhay Deol plays villain in Tamil film Hero, says it was 'a natural progression'|date=23 August 2019|website=Hindustan Times}}</ref>\n\nThe film was officially announced with its title ''Hero'' on 13 March 2019, with a formal pooja held, marking the commencement of the principal photography.<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n\n== Themes and influences ==\n''[[The Times of India]]'', reviewed the film as a spiritual sequel to ''[[Gentleman (1993 film)|Gentleman]]'' (1993).<ref name=\"TOI\">{{Cite web|url=http://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/tamil/movie-reviews/hero/amp_movie_review/72895272.cms|title=Hero Movie Review: Fairly good vigilante film, middling superhero movie|author=M Suganth|work=Times of India}}</ref> Some of the scenes and inventions used in the film were actually based on real-life incidents, which includes the [[Water-fuelled car|salt-water engine]] and satellites using [[helium]] filled balloon.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/sathishmsk/status/1209372347330809856?s=20|title=#Hero film speaks about the unsung heroes. Scenes have been inspired been inspired from real life incidents.|last=M|first=Sathish Kumar|date=2019-12-23|website=@sathishmsk|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Tiruchirapalli/students-launch-satellite-using-helium-filled-balloon/article26904440.ece|title=Students launch satellite using helium-filled balloon|last=Correspondent|first=Special|date=2019-04-21|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-01-12|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n\n==Music==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Hero\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = <div style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">21 December 2019 {{small|(Singles)}}<br/>9 January 2020 {{small|(Album)}}\n| recorded     = 2019\n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 15:20\n| language     = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| label        = [[Lahari Music]]<br>[[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| producer     = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| prev_title   = [[Nerkonda Paarvai]]\n| year         = 2019\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = \n}}\n\nThe soundtrack album is composed by Yuvan Shankar Raja, marking his second collaboration with Sivakarthikeyan and P. S. Mithran after \"[[Kedi Billa Killadi Ranga|Kedi Billa Killadi Ranga]]\" (2013) and ''[[Irumbu Thirai (2018 film)|Irumbu Thirai]]'' (2018) respectively. All the songs were released as singles, before being released as an album. The lyrics for the songs were written by [[Pa. Vijay]], [[Rokesh|G. Rokesh]] and rap versions were penned by Abby Simone and MC Sanna.\n\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = \n| title1 = Malto Kithapuleh\n| length1 = 3:43\n| title2 = Hero Title Track\n| length2 = 4:16\n| title3 = Overa Feel Pannuren\n| length3 = 3:44\n| title4 = Aayiram Mugangal\n| length4 = 3:41\n| title5 = \n| length5 = \n| title6 = \n| length6 = \n| title7 = \n| length7 = \n| title8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n| total_length = 15:20\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| extra1 = Shyam Vishwanathan\n| extra2 = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]], Abby Simone\n| extra3 = Yuvan Shankar Raja, MC Sanna\n| extra4 = [[Ilayaraaja]]\n| note2 = Rap versions by Abby Simone\n| note3 = Rap versions by MC Sanna\n| all_lyrics = [[Pa. Vijay]], except where noted\n| note1 = Lyrics written by [[Rokesh]]\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe film was released on 20 December 2019, clashing with ''[[Dabangg 3]]'', which was also distributed by KJR Studios.<ref name=\"reldate\" /> The film released in [[Dubai]] on 19 December 2019, a day before its original release.\n\n=== Distribution ===\nThe [[Tamil Nadu|Tamilnadu]] and [[Kerala]] distribution rights were acquired by the production house itself.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1207238561298206720?s=20|title=We are happy to announce the we will be doing the distribution of #Hero in the God's own country.|last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-18|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref> Horizon Studio acquired the [[Karnataka]] distribution rights. The overseas rights were bought by AP International and Home Screen Entertainment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GoldenCinemaGCC/status/1205115632196280322?s=20|title=.@Siva_Kartikeyan's #Hero directed by @Psmithran, music by @thisisysr, starring @akarjunofficial, @AbhayDeol & @kalyanipriyan, is all set to release in UAE & GCC on 19th December!|last=Cinema|first=Golden|date=2019-12-12|website=@GoldenCinemaGCC|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-17}}</ref>\n\n===Marketing===\nThe title poster, announcing the release date of the film was launched by the makers on 27 July 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/sivakarthikeyan-s-hero-release-date-announced-106269?amp|website=newsminute|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref> The first look was released on 2 September 2019, on the day of [[Ganesh Chaturthi|Vinayagar Chathurthi]], where Sivakarthikeyan was seen holding a mask.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/hero-first-look-poster-out-sivakarthikeyan-is-mysterious-in-ps-mithran-film-1594480-2019-09-02|title=Hero first-look poster out. Sivakarthikeyan is mysterious in PS Mithran film|newspaper=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11|agency=Ist}}</ref> The second look was released on 18 October 2019. Sivakarthikeyan is presented wearing mask with fire and chaos all around.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/sivakarthikeyan-in-hero-masked-crusader-or-superhero/article29736029.ece|title=Sivakarthikeyan in 'Hero': masked crusader or superhero?|first=The Hindu Net|last=Desk|date=18 October 2019|via=www.thehindu.com|newspaper=The Hindu}}</ref> The official teaser was launched by [[Salman Khan]] on 24 October 2019.<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=MB9Dj_YEMW0|title=Hero Official Teaser &#124; Sivakarthikeyan &#124; Arjun &#124; Yuvan Shankar Raja &#124; P.S.Mithran|work=Lahari Music|publisher=YouTube|date=24 October 2019}}</ref> The official trailer was released on 13th December 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://chennaiboxoffice.com/hero-official-trailer-sivakarthikeyan/|title=Hero Trailer|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nAs a part of the film's promotional purposes, the makers launched a new [[Augmented reality|Augmented Reality]] game experience titled Play Hero, on 23 November 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2019/nov/26/sivakarthikeyan-starrer-hero-gets-an-augmented-reality-game-2067009.html|title=Sivakarthikeyan-starrer 'Hero' gets an Augmented Reality game|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref> The latest poster of the film was launched on 28 November 2019. The production company KJR Studios, advertised the film in local trains, along with the Salman Khan-starrer ''[[Dabangg 3]]'', for which the distribution rights were bought by the company.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1203601078563901441?s=20|title=#HeroTrain maapla! |last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-08|website=@kjr_studios|language=et|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1203602712111116288?s=20|title=#Dabangg3 on wheels One of a kind train promotions for @BeingSalmanKhan's Tamil outing!|last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-08|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref> The makers also launched an one-of-a-kind upscale promotion, in which the \"Hero\" symbol is lighted up in buildings.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1203683802356207616?s=20|title=Testing something really UNIQUE & STUNNING for #Hero Know where this is?|last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-08|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref> \n\nOn 9 December 2019, the makers launched the official merchandise of the film teaming up with BeatRoute and Fully Filmy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1204045625165135873?s=20|title=We're stoked to be launching the official #HeroMerchandise of EXCLUSIVE COLLECTABLES ~Glow in the dark T-Shirt ~3D Embossed T-Shirt ~Pop grip ~Keychain ~Neck chain Shop now|last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-09|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref> Later the following day, on 10 December 2019, the makers released the [[WhatsApp]] stickers of the film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1204272148749012992?s=20|title=#HEROWAStickers out now! |last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-09|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref> On 11 December 2019, the makers launched the Augmented Reality filter for [[Facebook]] and [[Instagram]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1204634693313810432?s=20|title=Now you too can become a #Hero Check out #HeroARFilter for Facebook now!|last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-10|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1204637985792086017?s=20|title=Unleash the #Hero in you with #HeroARFilter Surprise, now out on Instagram too |last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-10|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref> Theatrical trailer of the film was released on 13 December 2019, at [[Sathyam cinemas|Sathyam Cinemas]] in [[Chennai]], and it was later released on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1204725164442701827?s=20|title=Much awaited. Much anticipated. We hope it'll be much loved too! #HeroTrailerlaunch event happening at Sathyam Cinemas on Friday at 8 AM. Releasing online at 11:03 AM|last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-11|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-13}}</ref> The makers also announced a promotional event at [[M. A. Chidambaram Stadium]], Chennai on 15 December 2019, coinciding with the [[West_Indian_cricket_team in India in 2019\u201320#1st_ODI|first ODI match between India and West Indies]] which was also hosted in Chennai.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1205136975000297473?s=20|title=GUESS WHAT'S HAPPENING THIS SUNDAY?|last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-12|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-13}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n''[[The Times of India]]'' rated the film 3.5 out of 5, stating that \"A superhero story origin, that's also a spiritual sequel to Shankar's ''Gentleman''\".<ref name=\"TOI\" /> Behindwoods rated the film 2.5 out of 5, stating that \"Hero is a watchable Super-Hero drama with some inspiring moments.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/hero/hero-review.html|title=Hero (aka) Sivakarthikeyan 15 review|date=2019-12-20|website=Behindwoods|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref> [[Firstpost]] rated the 3/5, stating that \"Mithran has given a neat commercial entertainer, which also calls for a rethink of our educational policy.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/hero-movie-review-sivakarthikeyan-takes-a-detour-from-romantic-comedies-but-film-isnt-thoroughly-convincing-7806971.html|title=Hero movie review: Sivakarthikeyan takes a detour from romantic comedies but film isn't thoroughly convincing- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=2019-12-20|website=Firstpost|language=en|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref> [[Sify]] rated the film 3.5 out of 5 stating that \"''Hero'' is a must watch for families this holiday season, which has a relevant message on the modern-day educational system.\"<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.sify.com/movies/hero-review-an-engaging-entertainer-for-families-review-tamil-tmujazajhjacc.html|title=Hero review: An-engaging-entertainer-for-families!!|last=|first=|date=22 December 2019|website=Sify|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n\n[[India Today]] rated the film 2.5 out of 5 stars, stating that \"Hero had all the potential to become a proper superhero film sensible to Tamil cinema standards. But, the lumbering narrative (in a few portions), exaggerated scenes and illogical loopholes ruin the entire experience.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/hero-movie-review-sivakarthikeyan-s-film-has-interesting-premise-but-let-down-by-execution-1629925-2019-12-20|title=Hero Movie Review: Sivakarthikeyan's film has interesting premise, but let down by execution|last=ChennaiDecember 20|first=Janani K.|last2=December 20|first2=2019UPDATED|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-01-12|last3=Ist|first3=2019 13:47}}</ref> Sudhir Srinivasan rated the film 3 out of 5 stars, stating that \"Hero takes its messaging very, very seriously. The film is a scathing criticism of the education system. It attacks colleges, pressurising parents, the spineless government, and above all, a syllabus that stifles originality and creativity, and in the words of Mahadev (Abhay Deol), \u201cthat is designed to create labourers.\u201d Moorthy (Arjun) says as much.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinemaexpress.com/reviews/tamil/2019/dec/20/hero-movie-review-sivakarthikeyan-arjun-kalyani-abhay-deol-ps-mithran-yuvan-shankar-raja-kjr-16150.html|title=Hero Movie Review: A gentleman trains a hero in this okayish origins film|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref> [[The Indian Express]] rated 2 out of 5 stating that \"Sivakarthikeyan\u2019s superpower is being super preachy.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/hero-movie-review-sivakarthikeyan-6176722/|title=Hero movie review: Sivakarthikeyan's superpower is being super preachy|date=2019-12-21|website=The Indian Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref> \n\n[[Baradwaj Rangan]] of [[Film Companion]] reviewed it as \"The film is surprisingly understated. It steers clear of massy \"hero\" moments, and there's a lot of clear, clean thinking in the writing.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmcompanion.in/hero-movie-review-ps-mithran-sivakarthikeyan-kalyani-priyadarshan-arjun-sarja-abhay-deol-baradwaj-rangan|title=Sivakarthikeyan's superhero saga needed more punch, but it's still solid|date=2019-12-20|website=Film Companion|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref> Haricharan Pudipeddi reviewed the film as \"PS Mithran\u2019s Hero is the Gentleman tribute we needed and it\u2019s a film that pretty much gets everything right.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinestaan.com/reviews/hero-41340|title=Hero review: Sivakarthikeyan-starrer is a Gentleman tribute that needed more punch|last=Pudipeddi|first=Haricharan|website=Cinestaan|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|id=10709232}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s action thriller films]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Indian action thriller films]]\n[[Category:2010s Indian superhero films]]\n[[Category:Indian vigilante films]]\n[[Category:2010s vigilante films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian 2019 Tamil-language superhero action thriller film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Hero\n| image          = Hero film poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[P. S. Mithran]]\n| producer       = Kotapadi J. Rajesh<br />T. Ezhumalaiyan\n| writer         = P. S. Mithran<br />[[Pon Parthiban]]<br />Savari Muthu<br />Antony Bhagyaraj\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Sivakarthikeyan]]\n*[[Abhay Deol]]<!-- DO NOT EDIT THE ORDER OF THE CAST. This is how the credits appeared in the movie-->\n*[[Arjun Sarja|Arjun]]\n*[[Kalyani Priyadarshan]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cinematography = [[George C. Williams (cinematographer)|George C. Williams]]\n| editing        = [[Ruben (editor)|Ruben]]\n| studio         = KJR Studios\n| released       = {{film date|2019|12|20|df=yes|}}\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Hero''''' is a 2019 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[superhero film]] directed by [[P. S. Mithran]], and produced by Kotapadi J. Rajesh under his production house KJR Studios. It stars [[Sivakarthikeyan]], [[Abhay Deol]], [[Arjun Sarja|Arjun]], [[Kalyani Priyadarshan]] and [[Ivana (actress)|Ivana]] in prominent roles. This film marks the Tamil debuts of Deol and Kalyani Priyadarshan.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/sivakarthikeyans-next-film-sk15-with-ps-mithran-is-titled-hero.html|title=Sivakarthikeyan's next film SK15 with PS Mithran is titled Hero|date=13 March 2019|website=Behindwoods}}</ref>\n\nThe story was written by P. S. Mithran, [[Pon Parthiban]], Savari Muthu and Antony Bhagyaraj. The music for the film is composed by [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]], with cinematography done by [[George C. Williams (cinematographer)|George C. Williams]], and editing done by [[Ruben (editor)|Ruben]]. The film was released worldwide on 20 December 2019.<ref name=\"reldate\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2019/sep/10/abhay-deols-tamil-film-hero-release-date-out-2031504.html|title=Abhay Deol's Tamil film 'Hero' release date out!|website=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nSakthivel \"Sakthi\" is a young boy who dreams of becoming a superhero, like [[Shaktimaan]]. After being ridiculed by his teacher and classmates for believing that Shaktimaan is real, Sakthi tries to prove it by falling off the terrace of his school, injuring himself in the process. His father ([[Azhagam Perumal]]) tries to convince Sakthi that Shaktimaan is fictional by showing the disclaimer of actor [[Mukesh Khanna]] advising viewers that the events depicted in the show are purely fictitious, causing Sakthi to abandon his hopes of becoming a superhero.\n \nYears later, Sakthi ([[Sivakarthikeyan]]) and Inbaraj \"Ink\" ([[Robo Shankar]]) are friends who earn their livelihood as educational brokers and run a xerox shop in their neighbourhood that houses a certificate [[forgery]] unit to help the needy secure their desired jobs at the expense of huge commissions. Sakthi bumps across Meera ([[Kalyani Priyadarshan]]), a social worker at an educational fair. and falls in love with her. Meera happens to be the inspiration of Mathi ([[Ivana (actress)|Ivana]]), a brilliant girl who aspires to become an [[aerospace engineering|aeronautical engineer]]. Mathi devises an engine that runs on saltwater as a measure to help her father ([[Elango Kumaravel]]) and many other thwart the problem of rising petrol prices. Meera soon learns of Sakthi's true profession and advises him to help Mathi secure an admission in an engineering college without any payment. Sakthi tries to secure an admission for Mathi, but to no avail. He learns that the only way to help Mathi secure a seat is to demonstrate the practical applications of her engine, which is rejected by Sathyamoorthy ([[Arjun Sarja|Arjun]]), Mathi's teacher who runs a school for the academically weak but brilliant children. Sakthi bypasses his warnings and demonstrates the engine at an educational fair by attaching it to an autorickshaw. This attracts the attention of the henchman of Mahadev ([[Abhay Deol]]). In turn, he promises a seat for Mathi with full scholarship. The next day, the autorickshaw is seized by the police, and Mathi is arrested on grounds of patent violation. The court convicts her guilty of the charges, which distraughts her. She attempts suicide by falling off a running train. Sakthi takes her to the hospital, only for the doctors to delay her treatment, and she eventually succumbs to her injuries. Sakthi and Ink are also convicted guilty and are placed on the wanted list for aiding Madhi. \n\nSakthi, on the run, decides that the only way to avenge Mathi's death and prove her innocence is to confront the company issuing the patents. Due to his experience in forging certificates, he easily fishes out the fact that the patent was forged by the company under Mahadev's orders but is attacked in the process, when he is rescued by Sathyamoorthy wearing a mask. Sathyamoorthy explains to him that Mahadev is a corrupt business tycoon whose aim is to wipe out innovation in work culture. He also subdues brilliant students and subjects them to [[lobotomy]], rendering their [[frontal cortex]] unusable, therefore reducing them to his \"puppets\". He uses their innovations to sell them to foreign companies and earn profits. Sathyamoorthy, being an advocate of innovation, secretly nurtures such children away from Mahadev in his school. Sakthi decides to fight the system along with Sathyamoorthy and the children, donning the mantle of the \"Mask.\"\n\nUsing the gadgets developed by the children and Sathyamoorthy's training, Sakthi fights through Mahadev's henchmen and eventually learns the truth. Sathyamoorthy sacrifices himself in the struggle, prompting Sakthi to telecast the innovative inventions of students and explaining to the audience that children should be given freedom to follow their passion and not be just mere bookworms. In the final fight, Mahadev's plans are foiled and Sakthi subjects him to lobotomy, disabling him permanently. Six months later, Sakthi, while still on the wanted list, runs the school along with Meera on the outskirts of the city. A police officer ([[Prem (actor)|Prem]]) approaches him and takes him in his jeep around the city, where Sakthi finds major developments in the city due to the innovations of Mathi and other brilliant students. The officer tosses away the documents relating to Sakthi's charges as he had opened his eyes about his child's dreams, and requests Sakthi to continue on with the mantle of the Mask.\nIn the post credits scene, it is also revealed that Sathyamoorthy is alive and is helping Sakthi in his missions.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Sivakarthikeyan]] as Sakthivel \"Sakthi\" / Hero (Mask)\n** Master Raghavan as young Sakthivel\n* [[Arjun Sarja|Arjun]] as Sathyamoorthy \"Moorthy\" (Sakthi\u2019s mentor) / Mask\n* [[Abhay Deol]] as Mahadev\n* [[Kalyani Priyadarshan]] as Meera\n* [[Ivana (actress)|Ivana]] as Mathi\n* Shyam Krishnan as Mahadev's assistant\n* [[Robo Shankar]] as Inbaraj \"Ink\"\n* [[Elango Kumaravel]] as Mathi's father\n* [[Azhagam Perumal]] as Sakthi's father\n* [[Prem (actor)|Prem]] as police officer \n* Ray Paul as Sathyamoorthy's student\n* Nithyaraj as Sathyamoorthy's student\n* Raja Rani Pandiyan as a TV viewer\n* Robo Chandru as a TV viewer\n* Shrawan as a TV viewer\n* Priya Rajkumar as a TV viewer\n* Douglas Kumaramoorthy as a private university HR manager\n* Supergood Subramani as the head master of Shakthi's childhood school\n* Mullai as Mullai, a resident of Sakthivel's area\n* Kothandam as a resident of Sakthivel's area\n* \"Black Sheep\" Ayaz as a helpline caller and in a special appearance in the song \"Overa Feel Pannuren\"\n* \"Unakennappa\" Vivek as a helpline caller and in a special appearance in the song \"Overa Feel Pannuren\"\n* P. S. Mithran in a special appearance as a fake certificates dealer\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\nAfter a successful debut through ''[[Irumbu Thirai (2018 film)|Irumbu Thirai]]'', director P. S. Mithran announced in early-2019 that he would direct a film  featuring actor [[Sivakarthikeyan]] in the lead role.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/sivakarthikeyan-ps-mithran-film-officially-announced-90982|title=Sivakarthikeyan-PS Mithran film officially announced|website=The News Minute|date=2 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/exciting-update-on-sivakarthikeyans-next-with-psmithran.html|title=Exciting Update on Sivakarthikeyan's next with P.S.Mithran|date=25 February 2019|website=Behindwoods}}</ref>\n\nThe crew of director Mithran's previous film, ''Irumbu Thirai'' were also retained for this film as well, including composer [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]], editor [[Ruben (editor)|Ruben]], cinematographer [[George C. Williams (cinematographer)|George C. Williams]]. Additionally, [[Arjun Sarja|Arjun]], who was the main antagonist in ''Irumbu Thirai'' was added to the cast.<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/sivakarthikeyan-to-lock-horns-with-arjun-sarja-for-thriller-1380900-2018-11-02|title=Sivakarthikeyan to lock horns with Arjun Sarja for thriller|date= 2 November 2018|website=India Today}}</ref> Furthermore,<ref name=\"auto\"/> later actress [[Kalyani Priyadarshan]] was announced to play the female lead alongside actress [[Ivana (actress)|Ivana]] in a supporting role. The film also marks Abhay Deol's Tamil debut, and he will be playing the main villain role for the first time in his career . <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/young-heroine-joins-the-cast-of-sivakarthikeyans-sk15.html|title=Young heroine joins the cast of Sivakarthikeyan's SK15|date=25 February 2019|website=Behindwoods}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/abhay-deol-plays-villain-in-tamil-film-hero-says-it-was-a-natural-progression-see-pics/story-37Htqb55BCANk46YIcg57J.html|title=Abhay Deol plays villain in Tamil film Hero, says it was 'a natural progression'|date=23 August 2019|website=Hindustan Times}}</ref>\n\nThe film was officially announced with its title ''Hero'' on 13 March 2019, with a formal pooja held, marking the commencement of the principal photography.<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n\n== Themes and influences ==\n''[[The Times of India]]'', reviewed the film as a spiritual sequel to ''[[Gentleman (1993 film)|Gentleman]]'' (1993).<ref name=\"TOI\">{{Cite web|url=http://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/tamil/movie-reviews/hero/amp_movie_review/72895272.cms|title=Hero Movie Review: Fairly good vigilante film, middling superhero movie|author=M Suganth|work=Times of India}}</ref> Some of the scenes and inventions used in the film were actually based on real-life incidents, which includes the [[Water-fuelled car|salt-water engine]] and satellites using [[helium]] filled balloon.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/sathishmsk/status/1209372347330809856?s=20|title=#Hero film speaks about the unsung heroes. Scenes have been inspired been inspired from real life incidents.|last=M|first=Sathish Kumar|date=2019-12-23|website=@sathishmsk|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Tiruchirapalli/students-launch-satellite-using-helium-filled-balloon/article26904440.ece|title=Students launch satellite using helium-filled balloon|last=Correspondent|first=Special|date=2019-04-21|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-01-12|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n\n==Music==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Hero\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = <div style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">21 December 2019 {{small|(Singles)}}<br/>9 January 2020 {{small|(Album)}}\n| recorded     = 2019\n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 15:20\n| language     = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| label        = [[Lahari Music]]<br>[[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| producer     = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| prev_title   = [[Nerkonda Paarvai]]\n| year         = 2019\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = \n}}\n\nThe soundtrack album is composed by Yuvan Shankar Raja, marking his second collaboration with Sivakarthikeyan and P. S. Mithran after \"[[Kedi Billa Killadi Ranga|Kedi Billa Killadi Ranga]]\" (2013) and ''[[Irumbu Thirai (2018 film)|Irumbu Thirai]]'' (2018) respectively. All the songs were released as singles, before being released as an album. The lyrics for the songs were written by [[Pa. Vijay]], [[Rokesh|G. Rokesh]] and rap versions were penned by Abby Simone and MC Sanna.\n\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = \n| title1 = Malto Kithapuleh\n| length1 = 3:43\n| title2 = Hero Title Track\n| length2 = 4:16\n| title3 = Overa Feel Pannuren\n| length3 = 3:44\n| title4 = Aayiram Mugangal\n| length4 = 3:41\n| title5 = \n| length5 = \n| title6 = \n| length6 = \n| title7 = \n| length7 = \n| title8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n| total_length = 15:20\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| extra1 = Shyam Vishwanathan\n| extra2 = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]], Abby Simone\n| extra3 = Yuvan Shankar Raja, MC Sanna\n| extra4 = [[Ilayaraaja]]\n| note2 = Rap versions by Abby Simone\n| note3 = Rap versions by MC Sanna\n| all_lyrics = [[Pa. Vijay]], except where noted\n| note1 = Lyrics written by [[Rokesh]]\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe film was released on 20 December 2019, clashing with ''[[Dabangg 3]]'', which was also distributed by KJR Studios.<ref name=\"reldate\" /> The film released in [[Dubai]] on 19 December 2019, a day before its original release.\n\n=== Distribution ===\nThe [[Tamil Nadu|Tamilnadu]] and [[Kerala]] distribution rights were acquired by the production house itself.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1207238561298206720?s=20|title=We are happy to announce the we will be doing the distribution of #Hero in the God's own country.|last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-18|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref> Horizon Studio acquired the [[Karnataka]] distribution rights. The overseas rights were bought by AP International and Home Screen Entertainment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GoldenCinemaGCC/status/1205115632196280322?s=20|title=.@Siva_Kartikeyan's #Hero directed by @Psmithran, music by @thisisysr, starring @akarjunofficial, @AbhayDeol & @kalyanipriyan, is all set to release in UAE & GCC on 19th December!|last=Cinema|first=Golden|date=2019-12-12|website=@GoldenCinemaGCC|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-17}}</ref>\n\n===Marketing===\nThe title poster, announcing the release date of the film was launched by the makers on 27 July 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/sivakarthikeyan-s-hero-release-date-announced-106269?amp|website=newsminute|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref> The first look was released on 2 September 2019, on the day of [[Ganesh Chaturthi|Vinayagar Chathurthi]], where Sivakarthikeyan was seen holding a mask.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/hero-first-look-poster-out-sivakarthikeyan-is-mysterious-in-ps-mithran-film-1594480-2019-09-02|title=Hero first-look poster out. Sivakarthikeyan is mysterious in PS Mithran film|newspaper=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11|agency=Ist}}</ref> The second look was released on 18 October 2019. Sivakarthikeyan is presented wearing mask with fire and chaos all around.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/sivakarthikeyan-in-hero-masked-crusader-or-superhero/article29736029.ece|title=Sivakarthikeyan in 'Hero': masked crusader or superhero?|first=The Hindu Net|last=Desk|date=18 October 2019|via=www.thehindu.com|newspaper=The Hindu}}</ref> The official teaser was launched by [[Salman Khan]] on 24 October 2019.<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=MB9Dj_YEMW0|title=Hero Official Teaser &#124; Sivakarthikeyan &#124; Arjun &#124; Yuvan Shankar Raja &#124; P.S.Mithran|work=Lahari Music|publisher=YouTube|date=24 October 2019}}</ref> The official trailer was released on 13th December 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://chennaiboxoffice.com/hero-official-trailer-sivakarthikeyan/|title=Hero Trailer|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nAs a part of the film's promotional purposes, the makers launched a new [[Augmented reality|Augmented Reality]] game experience titled Play Hero, on 23 November 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2019/nov/26/sivakarthikeyan-starrer-hero-gets-an-augmented-reality-game-2067009.html|title=Sivakarthikeyan-starrer 'Hero' gets an Augmented Reality game|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref> The latest poster of the film was launched on 28 November 2019. The production company KJR Studios, advertised the film in local trains, along with the Salman Khan-starrer ''[[Dabangg 3]]'', for which the distribution rights were bought by the company.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1203601078563901441?s=20|title=#HeroTrain maapla! |last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-08|website=@kjr_studios|language=et|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1203602712111116288?s=20|title=#Dabangg3 on wheels One of a kind train promotions for @BeingSalmanKhan's Tamil outing!|last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-08|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref> The makers also launched an one-of-a-kind upscale promotion, in which the \"Hero\" symbol is lighted up in buildings.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1203683802356207616?s=20|title=Testing something really UNIQUE & STUNNING for #Hero Know where this is?|last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-08|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref> \n\nOn 9 December 2019, the makers launched the official merchandise of the film teaming up with BeatRoute and Fully Filmy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1204045625165135873?s=20|title=We're stoked to be launching the official #HeroMerchandise of EXCLUSIVE COLLECTABLES ~Glow in the dark T-Shirt ~3D Embossed T-Shirt ~Pop grip ~Keychain ~Neck chain Shop now|last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-09|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref> Later the following day, on 10 December 2019, the makers released the [[WhatsApp]] stickers of the film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1204272148749012992?s=20|title=#HEROWAStickers out now! |last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-09|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref> On 11 December 2019, the makers launched the Augmented Reality filter for [[Facebook]] and [[Instagram]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1204634693313810432?s=20|title=Now you too can become a #Hero Check out #HeroARFilter for Facebook now!|last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-10|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1204637985792086017?s=20|title=Unleash the #Hero in you with #HeroARFilter Surprise, now out on Instagram too |last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-10|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref> Theatrical trailer of the film was released on 13 December 2019, at [[Sathyam cinemas|Sathyam Cinemas]] in [[Chennai]], and it was later released on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1204725164442701827?s=20|title=Much awaited. Much anticipated. We hope it'll be much loved too! #HeroTrailerlaunch event happening at Sathyam Cinemas on Friday at 8 AM. Releasing online at 11:03 AM|last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-11|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-13}}</ref> The makers also announced a promotional event at [[M. A. Chidambaram Stadium]], Chennai on 15 December 2019, coinciding with the [[West_Indian_cricket_team in India in 2019\u201320#1st_ODI|first ODI match between India and West Indies]] which was also hosted in Chennai.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kjr_studios/status/1205136975000297473?s=20|title=GUESS WHAT'S HAPPENING THIS SUNDAY?|last=Studios|first=K. J. R.|date=2019-12-12|website=@kjr_studios|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-13}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n''[[The Times of India]]'' rated the film 3.5 out of 5, stating that \"A superhero story origin, that's also a spiritual sequel to Shankar's ''Gentleman''\".<ref name=\"TOI\" /> Behindwoods rated the film 2.5 out of 5, stating that \"Hero is a watchable Super-Hero drama with some inspiring moments.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/hero/hero-review.html|title=Hero (aka) Sivakarthikeyan 15 review|date=2019-12-20|website=Behindwoods|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref> [[Firstpost]] rated the 3/5, stating that \"Mithran has given a neat commercial entertainer, which also calls for a rethink of our educational policy.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/hero-movie-review-sivakarthikeyan-takes-a-detour-from-romantic-comedies-but-film-isnt-thoroughly-convincing-7806971.html|title=Hero movie review: Sivakarthikeyan takes a detour from romantic comedies but film isn't thoroughly convincing- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=2019-12-20|website=Firstpost|language=en|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref> [[Sify]] rated the film 3.5 out of 5 stating that \"''Hero'' is a must watch for families this holiday season, which has a relevant message on the modern-day educational system.\"<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.sify.com/movies/hero-review-an-engaging-entertainer-for-families-review-tamil-tmujazajhjacc.html|title=Hero review: An-engaging-entertainer-for-families!!|last=|first=|date=22 December 2019|website=Sify|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n\n[[India Today]] rated the film 2.5 out of 5 stars, stating that \"Hero had all the potential to become a proper superhero film sensible to Tamil cinema standards. But, the lumbering narrative (in a few portions), exaggerated scenes and illogical loopholes ruin the entire experience.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/hero-movie-review-sivakarthikeyan-s-film-has-interesting-premise-but-let-down-by-execution-1629925-2019-12-20|title=Hero Movie Review: Sivakarthikeyan's film has interesting premise, but let down by execution|last=ChennaiDecember 20|first=Janani K.|last2=December 20|first2=2019UPDATED|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-01-12|last3=Ist|first3=2019 13:47}}</ref> Sudhir Srinivasan rated the film 3 out of 5 stars, stating that \"Hero takes its messaging very, very seriously. The film is a scathing criticism of the education system. It attacks colleges, pressurising parents, the spineless government, and above all, a syllabus that stifles originality and creativity, and in the words of Mahadev (Abhay Deol), \u201cthat is designed to create labourers.\u201d Moorthy (Arjun) says as much.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinemaexpress.com/reviews/tamil/2019/dec/20/hero-movie-review-sivakarthikeyan-arjun-kalyani-abhay-deol-ps-mithran-yuvan-shankar-raja-kjr-16150.html|title=Hero Movie Review: A gentleman trains a hero in this okayish origins film|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref> [[The Indian Express]] rated 2 out of 5 stating that \"Sivakarthikeyan\u2019s superpower is being super preachy.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/hero-movie-review-sivakarthikeyan-6176722/|title=Hero movie review: Sivakarthikeyan's superpower is being super preachy|date=2019-12-21|website=The Indian Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref> \n\n[[Baradwaj Rangan]] of [[Film Companion]] reviewed it as \"The film is surprisingly understated. It steers clear of massy \"hero\" moments, and there's a lot of clear, clean thinking in the writing.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmcompanion.in/hero-movie-review-ps-mithran-sivakarthikeyan-kalyani-priyadarshan-arjun-sarja-abhay-deol-baradwaj-rangan|title=Sivakarthikeyan's superhero saga needed more punch, but it's still solid|date=2019-12-20|website=Film Companion|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref> Haricharan Pudipeddi reviewed the film as \"PS Mithran\u2019s Hero is the Gentleman tribute we needed and it\u2019s a film that pretty much gets everything right.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinestaan.com/reviews/hero-41340|title=Hero review: Sivakarthikeyan-starrer is a Gentleman tribute that needed more punch|last=Pudipeddi|first=Haricharan|website=Cinestaan|access-date=2020-01-12}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|id=10709232}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s action thriller films]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Indian action thriller films]]\n[[Category:2010s Indian superhero films]]\n[[Category:Indian vigilante films]]\n[[Category:2010s vigilante films]]\n", "name_user": "Thinkwiki", "label": "safe", "comment": "Budget and Gross updated", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hero_(2019_Tamil_film)"}
{"title_page": "Bill Anderson discography", "text_new": "{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist          = [[Bill Anderson (singer)|Bill Anderson]]\n| Image           = Bill Anderson-Opry.jpg\n| Caption         = Bill Anderson at the [[Grand Ole Opry]], 2006.\n| Studio          = 45\n| Live            = 3\n| Compilation     = 10\n| Music videos    = 4\n| Singles         = 80\n| Option          = 6\n| Option name     = Other charted songs\n}}\nThe [[discography]] of American [[country music|country]] [[singer-songwriter]] [[Bill Anderson (singer)|Bill Anderson]] contains 45 [[studio album]]s, three [[live album]]s, ten [[compilation album]]s, four [[music video]]s, 80 [[single (music)|singles]] and six other charted songs. First a successful songwriter, Anderson got his own recording contract with [[Decca Records]] in 1958. His first singles were successful, beginning with \"That's What It's Like to Be Lonesome\". He had his first top ten hit on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot Country Singles|country songs]] chart with \"[[The Tip of My Fingers]]\" (1960).<ref name=\"Allmusic Bio\">{{cite web |last1=Huey |first1=Steve |title=Bill Anderson: Biography & History |url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/bill-anderson-mn0000057923/biography |website=[[Allmusic]] |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> This was followed by the top ten hits \"Walk Out Backwards\" (1960) and \"Po Folks\" (1962). His first single to top the ''Billboard'' country chart was 1962's \"[[Mama Sang a Song]]\".<ref name=\"Allmusic Bio\"/> In 1963, Anderson released his most successful single, \"[[Still (Bill Anderson song)|Still]]\". The song topped the country songs chart in April 1963,<ref>{{cite web |title=\"Still\" chart history |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/bill-anderson/chart-history/CSI/song/577036 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>, reached number 8 on the [[Billboard Hot 100]]<ref name=\"Allmusic Bio\"/> and peaked at number three on the [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|adult contemporary]] chart.<ref>{{cite web |title=\"Still\" chart history: Adult Contemporary |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/bill-anderson/chart-history/ASI/song/577036 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> A studio album of the [[Still (Bill Anderson album)|same name]] peaked at number 36 on the [[Billboard 200]], Anderson's only album to place on that chart.<ref name=\"Pop\">{{cite web |title=Bill Anderson Chart History: Billboard 200 |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/bill-anderson/chart-history/TLP |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nDuring the remainder of the 1960s, Anderson had a series of top ten singles on the ''Billboard'' country songs chart. Among these songs were the number one singles \"8\u00d710\" (1963), \"[[I Get the Fever]]\" (1966), and \"[[My Life (Throw It Away If I Want To)]]\".<ref name=\"Allmusic Bio\"/> Decca Records also issued several studio albums by Anderson in the 1960s. Among the highlights was ''[[I Love You Drops]]'' (1966), which topped the ''Billboard'' [[Top Country Albums|country albums]] chart.<ref>{{cite web |title=''I Love You Drops'' chart history |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/bill-anderson/chart-history/CLP/song/831773 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> Another notable release was ''My Life/But You Know I Love You'', which peaked at number four on the same chart in September 1969.<ref>{{cite web |title=''My Life/But You Know I Love You'' chart history |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/bill-anderson/chart-history/CLP/song/832050 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> Anderson would also collaborate with [[Jan Howard]] during this time. Their 1967 single \"[[For Loving You]]\" reached number one on the country songs chart.<ref name=\"Allmusic Bio\"/> Their corresponding [[For Loving You (album)|album]] peaked at number 6 in March 1973.<ref>{{cite web |title=''For Loving You'' chart history |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/bill-anderson/chart-history/CLP/song/831618 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> Anderson continued having top ten hits into the 1970s. This included the number one hits \"[[World of Make Believe]]\" (1973) and \"[[Sometimes (Bill Anderson song)|Sometimes]]\" (1976). His 1978 single, \"[[I Can't Wait Any Longer]]\" was his final top ten hit as recording artist.<ref name=\"Allmusic Bio\"/> \n\nAnderson continued recording with Decca (now [[MCA Records|MCA]]) into the 1980s. His final studio release with the label was ''Nashville Mirrors'' (1980).<ref>{{cite web |title=Bill Anderson -- ''Nashville Mirrors'' (1980, Vinyl) |url=https://www.discogs.com/Bill-Anderson-Nashville-Mirrors/release/1555806 |website=[[Discogs]] |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> He also continued recording sporadically during the decade. This included the release of ''A Place in the Country'' on his own label in 1986.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bill Anderson -- ''A Place in the Country'' (1986, Vinyl) |url=https://www.discogs.com/Bill-Anderson-A-Place-In-The-Country/master/1673947 |website=[[Discogs]] |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> Singles by Anderson were also being issued during the 1980s. His final chart appearance was a remake of \"[[The Deck of Cards]]\" in 1991. The single peaked at number 60 that February.<ref>{{cite web |title=\"Deck of Cards\" chart history |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/bill-anderson/chart-history/CSA |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> In 1998, he released his first major-label studio album in many years entitled ''Fine Wine''.<ref name=\"Allmusic Bio\"/> This led to Anderson releasing a series of studio albums for various labels over the next decade. His most recent studio release was ''Anderson'' (2018) on the TWI label.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bill Anderson: Album Discography |url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/bill-anderson-mn0000057923/discography |website=[[Allmusic]] |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Albums==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n|+ List of albums, with selected chart positions, showing other relevant details\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:19em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"3\"| Peak chart<br />positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Billboard 200|US]]<br /><ref name=\"Pop\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Top Country Albums|US<br />{{Small|Country}}]]<br /><ref name=\"Country Albums\">{{cite web |title=Bill Anderson: Country Albums |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/bill-anderson/chart-history/CLP |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[RPM (magazine)|CAN<br />{{Small|Country}}]]<br /><ref>{{cite web |title=Search results for \"Bill Anderson\" -- Country Albums/CDs |url=https://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/list.aspx?OCRText=Bill+Anderson&ChartEn=Country+Albums%2fCDs& |website=[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]] |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Still (Bill Anderson album)|Still]]''\n|\n* Released: June 1963\n* Label: [[Decca Records|Decca]]\n* Formats: [[Gramophone record|LP]]\n| 36 || 10 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Bill Anderson Sings]]''\n|\n* Released: February 1964\n* Label: Decca\n* Formats: LP\n| \u2014 || 7 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Showcase (Bill Anderson album)|Showcase]]''\n|\n* Released: November 1964\n* Label: Decca\n* Formats: LP\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Bright Lights and Country Music]]''\n|\n* Released: November 1965\n* Label: Decca\n* Formats: LP\n| \u2014 || 6 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[I Lov