 \ud83d\ude0a}}</ref>\n|Scott Dreier (2001\u20132004)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scottdreier.com/about/|title=About|website=Scott Dreier|accessdate=16 February 2018}}</ref>\n|[[Dan Green (voice actor)|Dan Green]] (2003\u201310)\n|[[Travis Willingham]] (2010\u201319)<ref name=\"behindthevoiceactors.com2\">{{cite web|title=Voice Of Knuckles the Echidna - Sonic Colors|url=http://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/video-games/Sonic-Colors/Knuckles-the-Echidna/|website=Behind The Voice Actors|accessdate=17 July 2017}}</ref>\n|[[Dave B. Mitchell]] (2019\u2013present)<ref name=\"behindthevoiceactors.com4\">{{cite web|title=Voice Of Knuckles the Echidna - Team Sonic Racing|url=https://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/video-games/Team-Sonic-Racing/Knuckles-the-Echidna/|website=Behind The Voice Actors|accessdate=19 June 2019}}</ref>}}\n{{Collapsible list|title='''[[Japanese language|Japanese]]'''\n|[[Yasunori Matsumoto]] (1996)\n|[[Nobutoshi Canna]] (1998\u2013present)}}\n}}\n{{nihongo|'''Knuckles the Echidna'''|\u30ca\u30c3\u30af\u30eb\u30ba\u30fb\u30b6\u30fb\u30a8\u30ad\u30c9\u30a5\u30ca|Nakkuruzu za Ekiduna|lead=yes}} is a [[fictional character]] in [[Sega]]'s ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog]]'' series. He is a red [[anthropomorphic]] [[echidna]] who is determined and serious, but sometimes gullible. He has the ability to glide and climb up walls, and is a powerful fighter with spiked hands. He serves as the guardian of the Master Emerald, a huge gemstone that controls the series' integral [[Chaos Emeralds]].\n\nKnuckles debuted in ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog 3]]'' in 1994 after [[Doctor Eggman]] tricks him into opposing [[Sonic the Hedgehog (character)|Sonic]] and [[Tails (character)|Tails]]. He first became playable in ''[[Sonic & Knuckles]]'' later that year; he learns of Eggman's trickery and teams up with Sonic and Tails during that game's events. Since then he has appeared in dozens of playable and non-playable roles, as well as in several series of [[comic book]]s, Western animated television, and Japanese [[anime]].\n\nKnuckles is one of the series' most popular characters, although some have voiced disapproval of the [[List of Sonic the Hedgehog characters|'' Sonic'' series' extensive cast of characters]] and singled out Knuckles as ushering them in.<ref>{{cite web|title=Where Did Sonic Go Wrong?|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2009/02/20/where-did-sonic-go-wrong?page=2|website=IGN|accessdate=12 March 2017|date=2009-02-20}}</ref> His likeness has frequently appeared in ''Sonic'' merchandise.\n\n==Concept and creation==\nDuring conception of ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog 3]]'', the development team wanted to create a new rival for Sonic.<ref name=\"Naka interview 96\">{{cite web |url=http://www.sega.com/features/allsonic/creator/naka04.html |title=Sonic's Creator - Yuji Naka|publisher=Sega.com|accessdate=August 28, 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/19970605172353/http://www.sega.com/features/allsonic/creator/naka04.html |archivedate=June 5, 1997}}</ref> The final design of Knuckles was the result of dozens of possible designs inspired by numerous different animals.<ref name=\"Naka interview 96\"/><ref name=\"sost\">{{cite web |url=http://sost.emulationzone.org/sonic_3/interview/rogerhector.htm |title=Secrets of Sonic Team: Interview with Roger Hector, former Director of Sega Technical Institute|accessdate=February 28, 2008|publisher=EmulationZone}}</ref> The emphasis of the character was to break walls.<ref name=\"Naka interview PPF\">{{cite web|url=http://www2.sega.com/sonic/globalsonic/post_sonicteam.php?article=nakainterviewsonic |publisher=Sega.com |title=Sonic Central interview: Yuji Naka on Sonic's Past, Present, Future |accessdate=July 7, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100526174339/http://www2.sega.com/sonic/globalsonic/post_sonicteam.php?article=nakainterviewsonic |archivedate=May 26, 2010 }}</ref> He was originally planned to have a [[Jamaican English|Jamaican accent]] and a name called \"Dreds\", referring to his dreadlocks.<ref>{{cite book|title=Sonic Advance 2: Prima's Official Strategy Guide|publisher=[[Prima Games]]|date=March 11, 2003|last=Mylonas|first=Eric|isbn=978-0761540083|page=99}}</ref>\n\nKnuckles was created by developer Takashi Yuda, who never intended him to be any more than a \"supporting character\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://xbox.gamespy.com/xbox/sonic-riders/683757p1.html|publisher=[[GameSpy]]|date=January 27, 2006|last=Theobald|first=Phil|title=Sega Talks Sonic Riders Part Two|accessdate=April 2, 2014}}</ref> Knuckles was introduced in ''Sonic the Hedgehog 3'' as an \"intimidator\" because of his powerful abilities and physical strength.<ref name=\"IGN Bio\">{{cite web|title=Knuckles the Echidna Biography|url=http://stars.ign.com/objects/962/962521_biography.html|website=IGN|accessdate=October 26, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140304040140/http://www.ign.com/characters/knuckles-the-echidna|archivedate=March 4, 2014}}</ref> He was given a headlining role in the next game, ''Sonic & Knuckles'', where he made his first appearance as a playable character.<ref name=\"IGN smash\">{{cite web |url=http://wii.ign.com/articles/827/827234p1.html|title=Smash It Up! - Sonic Team|website=IGN|date=October 12, 2007 |last=Thomas|first=Lucas M.|accessdate=October 26, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Characteristics==\nKnuckles is a 15-year-old red [[anthropomorphism|anthropomorphic]] [[echidna]], the only living descendant of a well-established clan of echidnas.<ref name=\"EUR profile\"/> For many years, his clan guarded a giant gemstone called the Master Emerald, which controls the [[Chaos Emeralds]], objects central to the ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog]]'' game series.<ref name=\"jp profile\">{{cite web |url=http://sonic.sega.jp/chara/Knuckles/index.html |script-title=ja:\u30ca\u30c3\u30af\u30eb\u30ba\u30fb\u30b6\u30fb\u30a8\u30ad\u30c9\u30a5\u30ca|language=Japanese|publisher=Sonic.sega.jp|accessdate=January 8, 2007|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20061231041629/http://sonic.sega.jp/chara/knuckles/index.html |archivedate=December 31, 2006}}</ref> As such, Knuckles has spent most of his life atop a [[Floating island (fiction)|floating island]] called Angel Island, guarding the Emerald from harm.<ref name=\"Sonic Adventure 2 profile\">''[[Sonic Adventure 2]]'' (Dreamcast) instruction manual, pp. 10\u201311.</ref> He has grown up fairly [[extraversion and introversion|introverted]] as a result.<ref name=\"EUR profile\"/>\n\nKnuckles has a serious, determined personality, described as keeping cool in combat.<ref name=\"Sonic Central\"/> However, he sometimes loses his composure and gets in fights with [[List of Sonic the Hedgehog video game characters|other characters]], and is sometimes shy around girls.<ref name=\"Sonic Jam profile\">[[Sega]] (1997). ''[[Sonic Jam]]'', Sega Saturn. Sonic World's Character Profiles (in [[English language|English]])</ref> His favorite food is [[grape]]s. His relationship with [[Sonic the Hedgehog (character)|Sonic]] is ambivalent: Knuckles enters the series as an antagonist of Sonic and later sees him as both a friend and a rival,<ref name=\"GSpy Naka\">{{cite web |url=http://ps2.gamespy.com/articles/654/654749p1.html |last=Kemps|first=Heidi|title=Sega's Yuji Naka Talks! |accessdate=October 26, 2014 |publisher=[[GameSpy]] |date=September 30, 2005}}</ref><ref name=\"Advance 3\"/><ref name=\"Heroes\">[[Sega]] (2003). ''[[Sonic Heroes]]'' instruction manual, pp. 7\u20138.</ref> while envying Sonic's adventurous lifestyle.<ref name=\"Sonic Central\">{{cite web|author=Sega of America |publisher=Sega.com |url=http://www.sega.com/sonic/globalsonic/post_allabout.php?article=soniccharacters |title=Sonic's official character profile from Sega of America |accessdate=March 10, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090217221441/http://www.sega.com/sonic/globalsonic/post_allabout.php?article=soniccharacters |archivedate=February 17, 2009 }}</ref> He is depicted as somewhat gullible and very rash, especially when angered.<ref name=\"jp profile\"/><ref name=\"bright\"/> He has often been tricked by [[Doctor Robotnik]], but is stated in one game manual to have become more skeptical of him.<ref>''[[Sonic Riders: Zero Gravity]]'' (Wii) instruction manual, p. 4.</ref>\n\nWhile slower than Sonic, Knuckles is depicted as one of the series' strongest characters and a skilled [[martial arts|martial artist]]: his brawny physique allows him to lift objects many times his size and weight, while his powerful fists enable him to smash through boulders.<ref name=\"EUR profile\">{{cite web |url=http://www.sonic-city.com/en/characters/knuckles/index.html |title=Sonic City|accessdate=March 4, 2008|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080225070243/http://www.sonic-city.com/en/characters/knuckles/index.html |archivedate = February 25, 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"jp profile\"/> He can also glide long distances by trapping air under his [[dreadlock]]s, and can climb up walls using the spikes on his gloves.<ref name=\"jp profile\"/> Unlike Sonic, Knuckles is able to swim.<ref name=\"Advance 3\">[[Sega]] (2004). ''[[Sonic Advance 3]]'' instruction manual, pp. 12-13.</ref> As is typical among ''Sonic'' characters, Knuckles can roll into a ball to attack enemies.<ref name=\"Sonic & Knuckles\">[[Sega]] (1994). ''[[Sonic & Knuckles]]'' instruction manual, pp. 7\u20138.</ref> He also has an empowered \"[[Super transformation (Sonic the Hedgehog)|super]]\" form: using the Chaos Emeralds allows him to transform into Super Knuckles. Using the Super Emeralds allows him to transform into Hyper Knuckles.<ref name=\"chronicles super\">{{cite video game|title=[[Sonic Chronicles: The Dark Brotherhood]] |developer=Bioware |publisher=Sega |date= |platform=Nintendo DS |version= |level=Codex |isolang= |quote= }}</ref>\n\n==Appearances==\n\n===In video games===\n{{Video game timeline\n| 1994 = ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog 3|Sonic 3]] [[Sonic & Knuckles|& Knuckles]]''\n| 1995a = ''[[Knuckles' Chaotix]]''\n| 1995b = ''[[Tails Adventure]]''\n| 1996a = ''[[Sonic The Fighters]]''\n| 1996b = ''[[Sonic Blast]]''\n| 1997 = ''[[Sonic R]]''\n| 1998 = ''[[Sonic Adventure]]''\n| 1999 = ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog Pocket Adventure|Sonic Pocket Adventure]]''\n| 2000 = ''[[Sonic Shuffle]]''\n| 2001 = ''[[Sonic Adventure 2]]''\n| 2002 = ''[[Sonic Advance 2]]''\n| 2003 = ''[[Sonic Heroes]]''\n| 2004 = ''[[Sonic Advance 3]]''\n| 2005 = ''[[Shadow the Hedgehog (video game)|Shadow the Hedgehog]]''\n| 2006 = ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog (2006 video game)|Sonic the Hedgehog]]''\n| 2007 = ''[[Sonic and the Secret Rings]]''\n| 2008 = ''[[Sonic Chronicles]]''\n| 2009 = ''[[Sonic and the Black Knight]]''\n| 2010 = ''[[Sonic Colors]]'' (DS version only)\n| 2011 = ''[[Sonic Generations]]'' (Console/PC version only)\n| 2012 = ''[[Sonic & All-Stars Racing Transformed]]''\n| 2013a = ''[[Sonic Lost World]]''\n| 2013b = ''[[Sonic Dash]]''\n| 2014a = ''[[Sonic Boom: Rise of Lyric]]''\n| 2014b = ''[[Sonic Boom: Shattered Crystal]]''\n| 2015a = ''[[Sonic Runners]]''\n| 2015b = ''[[Sonic Dash 2: Sonic Boom]]''\n| 2016 = ''[[Sonic Boom: Fire & Ice]]''\n| 2017a = ''[[Sonic Runners Adventure]]''\n| 2017b = ''[[Sonic Mania]]''\n| 2017c = ''Sonic Forces: Speed Battle''\n| 2017d = ''[[Sonic Forces]]''\n| 2018a = ''Sonic Mania Plus''\n| 2018b = ''[[Super Smash Bros. Ultimate]]''\n| 2019 = ''[[Team Sonic Racing]]''\n}}\n\nKnuckles debuted in the 1994 [[Sega Genesis]] game ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog 3]]''. Knuckles joins the series' primary antagonist Dr. Robotnik after being tricked into thinking that Sonic is attempting to steal the Master Emerald; Knuckles fights Sonic at several points throughout the game. Robotnik's dishonesty is revealed late in ''[[Sonic & Knuckles]]'' when he steals the Master Emerald and attacks Knuckles.<ref name=\"ign sand\"/> A similar plot follows in ''[[Sonic Triple Trouble]]''.<ref>''[[Sonic Triple Trouble]]'' instruction manual, p. 2.</ref> While Knuckles' canonical playable debut comes in ''Sonic & Knuckles'', he is playable in ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog 2|Sonic 2]]'' and ''3'' via the Genesis' lock-on technology.<ref name=\"ign sand\">{{cite web|last=Thomas|first=Lucas M.|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2010/02/22/sonic-knuckles-review|title=Sonic & Knuckles Review|website=[[IGN]]|date=February 22, 2010|accessdate=March 13, 2014}}</ref> Knuckles starred in ''[[Knuckles' Chaotix]]'' for the [[Sega 32X]], in which he serves as the guardian of an island [[amusement park]] and rescues his friends\u2014collectively known as the [[Chaotix]]\u2014from Robotnik in 1995. He teams up with them individually, creating an unusual gameplay style involving two characters being tethered together.<ref>''[[Knuckles' Chaotix]]'' instruction manual, p. 2.</ref>\n\nEggman shatters the Master Emerald, thus freeing [[Chaos (Sonic the Hedgehog)|Chaos]] who appears before Knuckles, the pieces are scattered, and Chaos flees in ''[[Sonic Adventure]]''.<ref>{{cite video game|title=[[Sonic Adventure]]|developer=[[Sonic Team]]|publisher=Sega|date=September 9, 1999|quote='''Knuckles:''' Something's happened to the Master Emerald!}}</ref> To restore the Emerald, thereby protecting Angel Island,<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=September 9, 1999|quote='''Knuckles:''' Without the Master Emerald's power, this whole island will fall into the ocean!}}</ref> he searches through various expansive levels for pieces.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=September 9, 1999|quote='''Knuckles:''' It's up to me to find the missing pieces of the Master Emerald.}}</ref> At one point, he defeats Chaos,<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=September 9, 1999|quote='''Knuckles:''' It's that creature again! The same one I saw on my island.}}</ref> and Eggman tricks Knuckles into thinking that Sonic is trying to collect Emerald shards for his own purposes.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=September 9, 1999|quote='''Eggman:''' He's after the pieces of the Master Emerald, too!}}</ref> Knuckles finds Sonic holding two Chaos Emeralds he thinks are Master Emerald shards, and attacks him.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=September 9, 1999|quote='''Knuckles:''' All right! Put 'em up! Hand over the Emerald now!}}</ref> This knocks them out of Sonic's hands,<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=September 9, 1999|quote='''Sonic:''' Oh no! The Chaos Emeralds...!}}</ref> so Eggman shows up to steal them and leaves.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=September 9, 1999|quote='''Eggman:''' Ha! That's all there is to it. You guys are too easy!}}</ref> He initially stays on Earth to look for pieces while Sonic and [[Tails (character)|Tails]] follow Eggman,<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=September 9, 1999|quote='''Sonic:''' No problem, Knuckles! We'll take care of everything here.}}</ref> but later joins them aboard Eggman's airship, the Egg Carrier, after seeing a vision of there being more pieces on it.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=September 9, 1999|quote='''Knuckles:''' Hey look! It's Eggman's flying fortress. That's where the rest of the pieces must be.}}</ref> He finds the final pieces and is confronted by Chaos' final form,<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=September 9, 1999|quote='''Knuckles:''' No! It can't be! I guess he didn't get enough the first time!}}</ref> then returns to the Emerald's island to restore it.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=September 9, 1999|quote='''Knuckles:''' This should do it! Perfect. All is well, now! The Master Emerald and the island have been restored.}}</ref>\n\nEarly in ''[[Sonic Adventure 2]]'', Knuckles and [[Rouge the Bat|Rouge]] argue over the Emerald;<ref>{{cite video game|title=[[Sonic Adventure 2]]|developer=[[Sega Studio USA]]|publisher=Sega|date=June 19, 2001|quote='''Knuckles:''' What are you talking about? That Emerald's mine!}}</ref> she wants the pieces for her personal collection. Eggman tries to steal it,<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure 2|developer=Sega Studio USA|publisher=Sega|date=June 19, 2001|quote='''Rouge:''' Whaa... thief!}}</ref> so Knuckles shatters it aboard Eggman's hovercraft, sending the pieces every which way. He spends the game recollecting the pieces similarly to in ''Adventure''.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure 2|developer=Sega Studio USA|publisher=Sega|date=June 19, 2001|quote='''Knuckles:''' I did that to prevent the Master Emerald from being stolen, you idiot! If it's in pieces, I can restore it.}}</ref> He later helps Sonic, Tails, and Amy find Eggman's base inside a [[Egyptian pyramids|giant pyramid]],<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure 2|developer=Sega Studio USA|publisher=Sega|date=June 19, 2001|quote='''Knuckles:''' I saw Eggman go inside the pyramid and more importantly, I saw that bat girl go inside with him as well.}}</ref> and a key to an inner chamber housing a giant [[space shuttle]].<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure 2|developer=Sega Studio USA|publisher=Sega|date=June 19, 2001|quote='''Knuckles:''' What? Why do I have to find the key?}}</ref> He follows them to a giant space station called the ARK with it, where he again scuffles with Rouge over the Emerald.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure 2|developer=Sega Studio USA|publisher=Sega|date=June 19, 2001|quote='''Knuckles and Rouge in unison:''' Stop fooling around, and give me back MY Emeralds!}}</ref> He saves her from falling into a constructed pit of [[lava]];<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure 2|developer=Sega Studio USA|publisher=Sega|date=June 19, 2001|quote='''Rouge:''' Keep your hands to yourself! Don't touch me!}}</ref> she decides the shards are worthless and dismissively lets him keep them,<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure 2|developer=Sega Studio USA|publisher=Sega|date=June 19, 2001|quote='''Rouge:''' Fine, then just take them. They stink like echidnas do.}}</ref> so he reassembles the Emerald and runs off.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure 2|developer=Sega Studio USA|publisher=Sega|date=June 19, 2001|quote='''Knuckles:''' Finally.}}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure 2|developer=Sega Studio USA|publisher=Sega|date=June 19, 2001|quote='''Rouge:''' We should get going.}}</ref> The game's antagonist [[Gerald Robotnik]], Eggman's grandfather, initiates a program to send the ARK on a collision course with Earth as revenge for an attack on the ARK decades earlier,<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure 2|developer=Sega Studio USA|publisher=Sega|date=June 19, 2001|quote='''Gerald:''' All of you ungrateful humans who took everything away from me will feel my loss and despair!}}</ref> so Knuckles teams up with the other playable characters to reroute it.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Adventure 2|developer=Sega Studio USA|publisher=Sega|date=June 19, 2001|quote='''Knuckles:''' That's right. If I use this, we just might be able to stop the Chaos Emerald!}}</ref>\n\nKnuckles serves as a power-based character in ''[[Sonic Heroes]]'' alongside Sonic and Tails, who respectively represent speed and flight.<ref name=\"heroes 7\">''Sonic Heroes'' (GameCube) instruction manual, p. 7.</ref> They team up to defeat Eggman after receiving a letter saying that he will destroy the world in three days.<ref>{{cite video game|title=[[Sonic Heroes]]|developer=Sonic Team USA|publisher=Sega|date=January 5, 2004|quote='''Eggman:''' In 3 days, I will conquer the world. Think you can stop me?}}</ref> However, it turns out that Eggman is being impersonated by [[Metal Sonic]], whom all of the other characters defeat together.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Heroes|developer=Sonic Team USA|publisher=Sega|date=January 5, 2004|quote='''Eggman:''' Aaaa... If only we had the 7 Chaos Emeralds!}}</ref> Knuckles helps Sonic, Tails, [[Amy Rose]], and [[Cream the Rabbit]] stop Eggman from building an empire in the ''[[Sonic Advance|Sonic]] [[Sonic Advance 2|Advance]]'' [[Sonic Advance 3|trilogy]].<ref>''[[Sonic Advance]]'' (Game Boy Advance) instruction manual, p. 4.</ref><ref>''[[Sonic Advance 2]]'' instruction manual, p. 4.</ref><ref>''[[Sonic Advance 3]]'' instruction manual, p. 12.</ref> With the same team, Knuckles recurs in ''[[Sonic Riders]]'' and its two sequels; in each game, they participate in board-racing competitions together.<ref>{{cite video game|title=[[Sonic Riders]]|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=February 21, 2006|quote='''Knuckles:''' (about [[Wave the Swallow]]) Did she say red MUTT?!}}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|title=[[Sonic Riders: Zero Gravity]]|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=January 8, 2008|quote='''Knuckles:''' Anytime... Babylon Rogues.}}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|title=[[Sonic Free Riders]]|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=November 4, 2010|quote='''Knuckles:''' Step aside!}}</ref> In another team-based installment, the [[role-playing video game|role-playing game]] ''[[Sonic Chronicles: The Dark Brotherhood]]'', Knuckles is a playable character with a major role in the story. The game begins with Tails informing Sonic that Knuckles has been kidnapped, so a team beginning as Sonic, Tails, Amy, and Rouge must rescue him. He is eventually saved, and it is revealed that the echidna race is still alive in the form of the helpful Shade the Echidna and her villainous tribe, the Nocturnus.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/sonic-chronicles-the-dark-brotherhood-review/1900-6199160/|website=[[GameSpot]]|last=Stella|first=Shiva|title=Sonic Chronicles: The Dark Brotherhood Review|date=October 10, 2008|accessdate=October 26, 2014}}</ref>\n\nHe is a minor character in ''[[Sonic Rush]]'',<ref name=\"bright\">{{cite video game|title=[[Sonic Rush]]|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=November 15, 2005|quote='''Cream:''' He's a tough guy, but he isn't very bright.)}}</ref> where he accosts protagonist [[Blaze the Cat]] under the impression that she has stolen Chaos Emeralds.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Rush|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=November 15, 2005|quote='''Knuckles:''' I can sense their power here!}}</ref> In the [[Nintendo DS]] version of ''[[Sonic Colors]]'', Knuckles arrives at an amusement park Eggman has created after receiving a letter.<ref>{{cite video game|title=[[Sonic Colors]] (Nintendo DS)|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=November 16, 2010|quote='''Rouge:''' Are you saying you didn't come here because of one of Eggman's letters?}}</ref> Frustrated at having been tricked,<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Colors (Nintendo DS)|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=November 16, 2010|quote='''Tails:''' So, um, Knuckles? How'd he trick you this time?}}</ref> he challenges Sonic to a race as a mission,<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Colors (Nintendo DS)|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=November 16, 2010|quote='''Knuckles:''' Hey, I'll, uhh... Race you through that ride! C'mon, are you chicken?!}}</ref> but shortly learns that Rouge wrote the letter inviting him to the park. He has a short argument with Rouge.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Colors (Nintendo DS)|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=November 16, 2010|quote='''Rouge:''' Well, if you must know, I was the one who wrote that letter. Satisfied?}}</ref> Modern Knuckles gives Classic and Modern Sonic missions and helpful advice in ''[[Sonic Generations]]''.<ref>{{cite video game|title=[[Sonic Generations]]|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=November 1, 2011|quote='''Knuckles:''' Look carefully while you're on the Zip Line after the Warp Point. There's another Zip Line that'll lead to a path with a Red Star Ring.|level=Hub world (outside Sky Sanctuary)}}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|title=[[Sonic Generations]]|developer=Sonic Team|publisher=Sega|date=November 1, 2011|quote='''Mission description:''' Knuckles: Buried Treasure / Press Y to make Knuckles dig up Medals! Collect a set number and reach the goal in time!|level=Hub world (outside Sky Sanctuary)}}</ref> In ''[[Sonic Lost World]]'', Knuckles and [[Amy Rose|Amy]] look after forest animals while Sonic and Tails rescue the animals' friends.<ref>{{cite video game|title=[[Sonic Lost World]]|developer=Sonic Team|date=October 29, 2013|publisher=Sega|quote='''Amy:''' Sonic and Tails'll get your buddies back.}}</ref> Later, the Deadly Six, the game's antagonists, take control of one of Eggman's machines to drain life from the world,<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Lost World|developer=Sonic Team|date=October 29, 2013|publisher=Sega|quote='''Amy:''' It's like something in the sky is draining the life out of the world.}}</ref> and Amy and Knuckles die, but they are brought back to life when Sonic and Tails replenish it.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Sonic Lost World|developer=Sonic Team|date=October 29, 2013|publisher=Sega|quote='''Amy:''' Thanks to you and Tails.}}</ref> He is a playable character in ''[[Sonic Mania|Sonic Mania (Plus)]]'', regaining his role from the first games alongside Sonic, Tails, Mighty and Ray. He appears in the game ''[[Sonic Forces]]'', where he becomes the leader of a resistance created to fight back against Eggman's advancing forces.\n\nKnuckles has been a playable character in numerous spinoff games with little effect on the series' plot, such as the [[fighting game]] ''[[Sonic the Fighters]]'',<ref>''[[Sonic Gems Collection]]'' (GameCube) instruction manual, p. 5.</ref> the [[racing game|racing]] title ''[[Sonic R]]'',<ref>''Sonic Gems Collection'' (GameCube) instruction manual, p. 11.</ref> and the [[party video game|party]] title ''[[Sonic Shuffle]]'',<ref>''[[Sonic Shuffle]]'' instruction manual, p. 21.</ref> as well as crossover games like ''[[Mario & Sonic at the Olympic Games]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/games/mario-sonic-at-the-olympic-games/nds-896693|website=IGN|title=Mario & Sonic at the Olympic Games\n|accessdate=October 13, 2014}}</ref> and ''[[Sonic & All-Stars Racing Transformed]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/mario-kart-8-vs-sonic-racing-the-comparison-we-had-t-1610241058|publisher=[[Kotaku]]|title=''Mario Kart 8'' vs. ''Sonic Racing'': The Comparison We Had To Make|date=July 24, 2014|last=LeJacq|first=Yannick|accessdate=October 13, 2014}}</ref> He makes a cameo appearance in ''[[Sega Superstars Tennis]]'', as a member of the audience in the [[Green Hill Zone|Green Hill]] court<ref>{{cite video game|title=[[Sega Superstars Tennis]]|date=March 18, 2008|publisher=Sega|developer=[[Sumo Digital]]|level=Green Hill}}</ref> and in ''[[Super Smash Bros. Brawl]]''{{'s}} Green Hill stage, where he, Tails, and [[Silver the Hedgehog|Silver]] run through the [[vertical loop]] in the background.<ref>{{cite video game|title=[[Super Smash Bros. Brawl]]|date=March 9, 2008|publisher=[[Nintendo]]|developer=[[Sora, Ltd.]]|level=Green Hill Zone}}</ref> Knuckles appears as one of four playable characters in the [[action-adventure game|action-adventure]] spin-off property ''[[Sonic Boom (2014 video games)|Sonic Boom]]''.<ref name=\"scarf\">{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2014/2/6/5387184/why-sega-handed-sonic-over-to-western-studios-and-gave-him-a-scarf|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]|title=Why Sega handed Sonic over to Western studios and gave him a scarf|last=Corriea|first=Alexa Ray|date=February 6, 2014|accessdate=February 27, 2014}}</ref> In ''[[Lego Dimensions]]'', Knuckles appears as a non-playable character in the Sonic the Hedgehog world, in which he requests the player to assist him in a sidequest to take down some of Eggman's robots, during which he makes a number of references to the rap songs about him in the ''Sonic Adventure'' games. Knuckles also makes a cameo as an easter egg in ''[[Deus Ex: Mankind Divided]]'' on the box of a video game entitled ''Knuckles the Echidna in Knuckles & Knuckles & Knuckles''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pcgamer.com/deus-ex-mankind-divided-easter-eggs/|title=Deus Ex: Mankind Divided Easter eggs reference Portal, Sonic, and Mitt Romney|publisher=|accessdate=16 February 2018|date=2016-08-24}}</ref> In ''[[Super Smash Bros. Ultimate]]'', Knuckles appears as an assist trophy that attacks players when summoned; he also appears as a spirit.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Versus |first1=Nintendo |title=Knuckles the Echidna comes to Super #SmashBrosUltimate as an Assist Trophy! He'll pummel nearby fighters with his fists, and can attack from underground with a big uppercut! |url=https://twitter.com/NintendoVS/status/1013905209012244480 |website=twitter.com |accessdate=3 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n===In comics===\nIn ''[[Sonic the Comic]]'', Knuckles plays a similar role to that of the games. When the Death Egg crashes on Angel Island, Knuckles is briefly tricked by Dr. Robotnik<ref>{{cite comic|story=Knuckles: Guardian of the Chaos Emeralds|title=[[Sonic the Comic]]|issue=N/A (\"Sonic Holiday Special 1994\")|date=June 18, 1994, |publisher=[[Egmont Publishing]]}}</ref> and thus allows Robotnik to place his robot armies on the island and construct a base to rebuild his Death Egg.<ref>{{cite comic|story=Robotnik's Revenge, Part 1|title=Sonic the Comic|issue=37|date=October 28, 1994|publisher=Egmont Publishing}}</ref> Knuckles also assists him in fighting Sonic and stealing Sonic's own six Emeralds so they can be combined with Knuckles' into one set of Emeralds.<ref>{{cite comic|story=Power of the Chaos Emeralds, Part 1|title=Sonic the Comic|issue=35|date=September 30, 1994|publisher=Egmont Publishing}}</ref> However, Knuckles does not trust Robotnik enough to tell him that he possesses a seventh Emerald that can control the others, and when Robotnik tries to absorb the Emeralds' power into himself, Knuckles uses this Emerald to defeat him.<ref>{{cite comic|story=Power of the Chaos Emeralds, Part 2|title=Sonic the Comic|issue=36|date=October 13, 1994|publisher=Egmont Publishing}}</ref> From that point on, he works as an ally against Robotnik, starting by removing all traces of the doctor's influences from Angel Island.<ref>{{cite comic|story=Carnival Night Conspiracy, Part 1|title=Sonic the Comic|issue=39|date=November 25, 1994|publisher=Egmont Publishing}}</ref>\n\nIn the [[Sonic the Hedgehog (comics)|comic series of ''Sonic the Hedgehog'']] published by [[Archie Comics]], Knuckles is the eighteenth guardian of the Floating Island, which is also called Angel Island. He is also a member of the [[Brotherhood of Guardians]], a [[secret society]] that defends the island and is made up of Knuckles' predecessors/ancestors. In keeping with the incorporation of elements of the [[Sonic the Hedgehog (TV series)|'' Sonic the Hedgehog'']] cartoon into the series, Knuckles lives on the planet Mobius. Knuckles is supported in his efforts by the [[Chaotix]], and often works together with Sonic the Hedgehog and the Freedom Fighters.\n\nWhen Knuckles was first introduced he was the lone defender of the island, but differences between this continuity and the games were quickly introduced. Writer [[Ken Penders]] built up a considerable backstory for Knuckles, in which he is abandoned by his father, Locke, as part of his Guardian training. He was later tricked by Robotnik into believing that Sonic and Tails were on their way to steal the Chaos Emerald and its powers. After a short melee, Robotnik blatantly betrayed Knuckles, causing him to join Sonic in a begrudging team-up, which eventually grew into a strong friendship.\n\nNot too long after that, he formed the Chaotix along with Vector, out of the few refugee inhabitants on Angel Island at the time and would leave the island to their care if he ever had to leave. The Chaotix at the time were Knuckles the Echidna, Vector the Crocodile, Espio the Chameleon, Mighty the Armadillo, Charmy Bee, Heavy, and Bomb, but later saw the addition of Ray the Flying Squirrel, Julie-Su the Echidna (who became his love interest), and Saffron Bee (Charmy's betrothed), while Heavy and Bomb departed and later joined the King's Secret Service. Knuckles was also revealed to have a mystically significant destiny as \"the Avatar,\" corresponding to similar destinies shared by Tails and Sonic. He and Princess [[Sally Acorn]] were also revealed to be childhood friends, having met when she and her father paid a visit to the Floating Island while Knuckles' father was Guardian.\n\nAfter believing himself to be the last living Echidna for some time, Knuckles stumbled upon the existence of others; his earliest encounters with others of his people would earn him enemies. The first would be his great-uncle Dimitri, who had been possessed by a malevolent spirit and become an evil being known as Enerjak. He would then run across a cyborg army known as the Dark Legion-led by Dimitri's descendants-who had previously been banished to another dimension by one of the Knuckles' ancestors. Julie-Su started out as a member of this group but defected to join Knuckles after an Echidna sixth sense known as the Soultouch identified Knuckles as an ideal soul mate. Accompanied by Julie, Knuckles would come across others of his kind, including the city of Echidnaopolis-home to his mother after she divorced his father Locke-the Brotherhood of Guardians, and the hidden city of Albion.\n\nKnuckles' early adventures typically involved protecting Angel Island or the various Echidna groups-only rarely would he join the Freedom Fighters against threats like Dr. Robotnik. However, Robotnik's encroachments on different areas of the planet-including Angel Island itself-eventually persuaded Knuckles to relocate to the surface to join the battle against the evil doctor and other threats. One of his enemies-a villainous Echidna named Dr. Finitevus-later made Knuckles into a new Enerjak after revealing that Robotnik had driven the Echidna race to the brink of extinction. Knuckles would become wracked with guilt over his actions, especially since the remnants of the Dark Legion chose to ally themselves with Dr. Robotnik.\n\nThe final blow would come when Knuckles responded to a distress call from his people and arrived in Albion to find it deserted. This would be revealed to be the work of Thrash the Tasmanian Devil, whose people were mutated by ancient Echidnas. Thrash's actions led to almost all the remaining Echidnas being banished from Mobius, with Knuckles failing to rescue them. In reality, the disappearance of these characters-among others-was due to a lawsuit by Ken Penders.\n\nAs a result of the continuity reboot that followed the crossover with the ''[[Mega Man]]'' franchise, Knuckles became virtually indistinguishable from his video game counterpart: he is the last known Echidna and the last Guardian of Master Emerald, and the Chaotix no longer serve as his full-time support team.\n\n===In animation===\nKnuckles' animation debut came with the 1996 Japanese ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog (OVA)|Sonic the Hedgehog]]'' [[original video animation|OVA]]. Sonic and Tails meet him in an alternate dimension, and over the course of the film he helps them defeat Black Eggman/Metal Robotnik and [[Metal Sonic|Hyper Metal Sonic]], two robots created by Eggman/Robotnik. As Metal is about to descend into a lava pit, Sonic attempts to save him after all, but Knuckles holds him back and Sonic is disappointed. Knuckles play-fights with Sonic a few times in the film as well.<ref>{{cite AV media|title=[[Sonic the Hedgehog (OVA)|Sonic the Hedgehog: The Movie]]|year=1999|publisher=[[ADV Films]]|medium=DVD}}</ref>\n\nKnuckles is a minor character in ''[[Sonic Underground]]''. Sonic, Sonia, and Manic meet Knuckles atop his home, the Floating Island while searching for their mother. Knuckles is initially skeptical of them but soon accepts their help in protecting the Island and its guardian Chaos Emerald from villains Sleet and Dingo.<ref>{{cite episode|title=Friend or Foe?|episodelink=List of Sonic Underground episodes|series=[[Sonic Underground]]|airdate=January 18, 2000|season=1|number=18}}</ref> Later on, the siblings recruit Knuckles to help them deactivate Doctor Robotnik's giant fortress, as it is powered by Emeralds and he can control them.<ref>{{cite episode|title=Flying Fortress|episodelink=List of Sonic Underground episodes|series=Sonic Underground|airdate=March 22, 2000|season=1|number=27}}</ref> They succeed, but Sleet and Dingo accidentally break the Emerald, unleashing gradually effective but massive energy upon the planet Mobius, and Knuckles enlists one of his relatives to help them control it, with mediocre results.<ref>{{cite episode|title=No Hedgehog Is an Island|episodelink=List of Sonic Underground episodes|series=Sonic Underground|airdate=March 29, 2000|season=1|number=28}}</ref> Reluctantly, Knuckles cuts a deal with Robotnik to turn over the hedgehogs in exchange for setting Mobius right; Robotnik succeeds and starts turning the hedgehogs into robots, but Knuckles betrays Robotnik to rescue his friends.<ref>{{cite episode|title=New Echidna in Town|episodelink=List of Sonic Underground episodes|series=Sonic Underground|airdate=April 5, 2000|season=1|number=29}}</ref>\n\nKnuckles appears in all three seasons of ''[[Sonic X]]''. He takes guarding Master Emerald seriously and has a fearsome temper with a \"chip on his shoulder\". After being stranded in the new world with Sonic, his only desire is to get back home quickly.<ref name=\"4Kids characters\">{{cite web |url=http://www.4kids.tv/show/sonic-x/characters |title=Characters: Knuckles|accessdate=October 26, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120410060055/http://www.4kids.tv/show/sonic-x/characters|archivedate=April 10, 2012|publisher=4Kids.tv}}</ref> He spends most of the first season traveling alone, but as the series continues he begins to travel with Sonic and the others more often, as well as befriending other characters. After returning home for the third season, he joins Sonic on the spaceship, \"Blue Typhoon\", which is captained by Tails after their planet was invaded by the Metarex.\n\nKnuckles is among the main cast in the ''[[Sonic Boom (TV series)|Sonic Boom]]'' computer-animated series. He has been redesigned: now taller and more muscular than before.<ref name=\"scarf\"/> As a somewhat exaggerated reference to his mainstream counterpart's easily deceived personality (as well being based on the stereotypical team muscles), Knuckles is also portrayed as being somewhat slow-witted and goofy in this series.\n\n==Reception and impact==\nThe character has received positive attention. According to [[IGN]]'s Levi Buchanan, fans \"seemed legitimately happy\" with the addition of the character of Knuckles, who was popular enough to get marquee billing in ''[[Sonic & Knuckles]]'', but Buchanan felt that characters who came after him were going \"overboard\".<ref name=\"IGN wrong\">{{cite web |url=http://retro.ign.com/articles/955/955741p2.html |title=Where Did Sonic Go Wrong? |last=Buchanan|first=Levi|date=February 20, 2009 |accessdate=October 26, 2014}}</ref> IGN's Colin Moriarty singled out the introduction of both Knuckles and Tails as when the series became \"iffy\" and listed them and all other characters in the series, sans Sonic and Robotnik, as being 2nd most in need to \"die\" on his top 10 list.<ref name=\"IGN die\">{{cite web |url=http://pc.ign.com/articles/955/955079p1.html |author1=IGN PlayStation Team |author2=Moriarty, Colin |title=Wednesday 10: Video game Characters That Should Die |date=February 18, 2009 |accessdate=October 26, 2014}}</ref> In contrast, he was listed as the best ''Sonic'' character by ''[[Official Nintendo Magazine]]'' based on the impact he brought to the ''Sonic'' games in which he first appeared.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.officialnintendomagazine.co.uk/50022/features/the-best-and-worst-sonic-characters/?page=5|title=The best and worst Sonic characters|magazine=[[Official Nintendo Magazine]]|last=East|first=Thomas|accessdate=October 24, 2013|date=May 29, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029204405/http://www.officialnintendomagazine.co.uk/50022/features/the-best-and-worst-sonic-characters/?page=5|archive-date=October 29, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nAccording to official Sonic Team polls, Knuckles is the fourth most popular character in the series, following behind [[Miles \"Tails\" Prower|Tails]], [[Shadow the Hedgehog|Shadow]], and Sonic.<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120229160623/http://sonic.sega.jp/SonicChannel/event/016/002.html|archivedate=February 29, 2012|url=http://sonic.sega.jp/SonicChannel/event/016/002.html|script-title=ja:\u30bd\u30cb\u30c3\u30af\u30c1\u30e3\u30f3\u30cd\u30eb/\u30a4\u30d9\u30f3\u30c8/\u30bd\u30cb\u30c3\u30af \u30ad\u30e3\u30e9\u30af\u30bf\u30fc \u4eba\u6c17\u6295\u7968 \u7d50\u679c\u767a\u8868\uff01|language=Japanese|accessdate=October 26, 2014|date=June 23, 2006}}</ref> Elton Jones from ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]'' listed Knuckles as his eleventh most wanted character in the next ''[[Super Smash Bros. (Wii U/3DS)|Super Smash Bros.]]'' game.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.complex.com/video-games/2012/07/25-characters-we-want-to-see-in-super-smash-bros-brawl-4/knuckles-the-echidna |title=Knuckles the Echidna \u2014 25 Characters We Want To See In \"Super Smash Bros. Brawl 4\" |magazine=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]] |date=July 2, 2012|last=Jones|first=Elton |accessdate=August 2, 2012}}</ref> In another article, ''Complex'' regarded Knuckles as a better character than Sonic, and praised his gliding and climbing abilities, stating \"even if his levels were a little more challenging than Sonic's, the thrill of being able to explore certain parts of levels that the blue-colored hero could not be worth it\".<ref>{{cite magazine|author=Elijah Watson|url=http://www.complex.com/video-games/2014/02/knuckles-is-better-than-sonic-definitive-reasoning-20-year-anniversary-sonic-the-hedgehog-3 |title=Knuckles, Better Than Sonic, Definitive Reasoning 20 Year Anniversary, Sonic the Hedgehog |magazine=Complex |date=February 5, 2014 |accessdate=May 4, 2014}}</ref> Riley Little from GameRant included Knuckles on his list of the \"Top 10 Third-Party Characters that Could Appear in the New ''Super Smash Bros.''\", commenting \"This punch-drunk brawler knows how to serve up a buffet of knuckle sandwiches, and there\u2019s no question that he\u2019s one of the most fitting characters to occupy a spot on the roster\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gamerant.com/third-party-characters-super-smash-bros-4-riley-156631/5/|title=Top 10 Third-Party Characters that Could Appear in the New 'Super Smash Bros.'|last=Little|first=Riley|publisher=GameRant|date=July 10, 2012|accessdate=August 2, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120715232100/http://gamerant.com/third-party-characters-super-smash-bros-4-riley-156631/5/|archive-date=July 15, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n''[[Mega Zone]]''{{'}}s review of ''Knuckles' Chaotix'' praised the introduction of a new protagonist, whom it deemed \"rougher [and] tougher\" in comparison to the \"spineless\" Sonic.<ref name=\"megazone 2\">{{cite journal|journal=Mega Zone|title=Chaotix|author=Adam|issue=50|date=April 1995|page=22}}</ref> ''[[Mean Machines Sega]]'' called Knuckles' powers \"impressive\" and the character overall more useful and promising than Tails.<ref>{{cite magazine|magazine=[[Mean Machines Sega]]|title=Sonic & Knuckles|issue=24|page=16|publisher=EMAP}}</ref> ''[[Sega Magazine]]'' stated that Knuckles \"looks cooler\" than Sonic, comparing him to [[Spider-Man]], and suggested he be given his own game.<ref>{{cite magazine|magazine=[[Sega Magazine]]|title=Sonic cathedral of sound|publisher=EMAP|date=September 1994|issue=9|page=55}}</ref> ''Sega Magazine'' later called him \"groovy\" and \"ace\", concluding that they \"love him.\"<ref>{{cite magazine|magazine=Sega Magazine|title=Review|publisher=EMAP|date=October 1994|issue=10|page=80}}</ref> Knuckles' characterization in ''Sonic Boom'' earned praise by Polygon due to how \"progressive\" he is when mentioning [[feminism]] much to the shock of the characters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/tv/2017/8/2/16085836/sonic-the-hedgehog-knuckles-feminist-woke-cartoon|title=Sonic Boom gets progressive in one great moment|website=Polygon|accessdate=January 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikipedia books|Sonic the Hedgehog}}\n\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090217221441/http://www.sega.com/sonic/globalsonic/post_allabout.php?article=soniccharacters Sonic Central official character profiles]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20061231041629/http://sonic.sega.jp/chara/knuckles/index.html Knuckles at Sonic Channel] {{in lang|ja}}\n\n{{Sonic the Hedgehog}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Knuckles The Echidna}}\n[[Category: Animal characters in video games]]\n[[Category: Animal superheroes]]\n[[Category: Anthropomorphic animal characters]]\n[[Category: Anthropomorphic characters in video games]]\n[[Category: Anthropomorphic martial artists]]\n[[Category:Fictional boxers]]\n[[Category:Fictional fist-load fighters]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters who became a protagonist in a spin-off]]\n[[Category:Fictional monotremes]]\n[[Category: Male characters in video games]]\n[[Category: Sega protagonists]]\n[[Category: Sonic the Hedgehog characters]]\n[[Category: Teenage characters in video games]]\n[[Category: Video game bosses]]\n[[Category: Video game characters in comics]]\n[[Category: Video game characters in television]]\n[[Category: V